      "lineNbr": 199,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-03-13T02:27:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is an unfortunate side effect of the API and object model (which are both bad). The API protos and models don\u0027t line up, and so the query has a \"LogStreamState\" message which is partially from coordinator.LogStream and partially from coordinator.LogStreamState (which are separate entities for no reason that I can discern). For fun, the State boolean also controls the population of Desc, which doesn\u0027t reside in the LogStreamState response object.\n\nI\u0027ll see if I can clarify/add some commentary, but it\u0027s pretty bad.",
      "parentUuid": "b0a5ea4e_15ac3d7b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 199,
        "startChar": 24,
